{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"[operator-attested] DEPLOY COMPLETE + live checks pass (2026-07-15).\n\nterraform apply (account 896586841071, us-east-1): 9 resources added, 0 changed, 0 destroyed.\n  - API Gateway HTTP API: id p38uolodo3, endpoint https://p38uolodo3.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\n  - IAM role: arn:aws:iam::896586841071:role/rebar-opcert-admin (execute-api:Invoke scoped to the API)\n  - SSM SecureStrings: /rebar/prod/opcert-ed25519-key (Ed25519 signing key seeded), /rebar/prod/opcert-origin-guard\nAll AC1 jq plan-assertions pass against the applied state (a/b/c-d/e/f/g + sole-Invoke-grant).\nEnv pinned in .rebar/trusted_environments.yaml (env_id 9f1c8e42-..., real public key, log-position era anchor).\nService deployed on the rebar-gerrit box (compose-opcert-1 up, loopback :8090 behind API GW + host nginx /opcert/ guarded route). Gerrit remained HTTP 200 throughout (fail-safe nginx rollbacks protected it).\n\nLIVE CHECKS (all PASS):\n  1. SigV4-signed round-trip: POST /opcert/jobs -> 202 {job_id}; GET poll -> status=completed, verdict=PASS, envelope=<signed rebar.opcert.v1 DSSE> (job ca38092f). The trusted environment fetched authoritative state itself and signed.\n  2. Unsigned request to API GW -> HTTP 403 (IAM/SigV4 rejected).\n  3. Direct-to-origin /opcert/ without X-Opcert-Guard header -> HTTP 403 (nginx fail-closed).\nThree deploy blockers found by the real deploy + fixed (bug accc, changes #694 + #696): Dockerfile ssh -V, nginx map_hash_bucket_size, compose AWS_REGION."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784082256094280001,"uuid":"b9bbadd8-b380-4963-b02c-0bfb6d49c658"}